and I thought, I think in the earlier phases of my life,

234
00:11:57,920 --> 00:12:01,200
I sacrificed everything in this pursuit of becoming a millionaire

235
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:04,080
and having all this stuff and really getting this validation

236
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:06,160
sacrificed meaningful connections,

237
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,080
everything in the pursuit of this one thing.

238
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,920
Well, part of the toxicity of the culture

239
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:14,160
that I talk about in this book is that it actually rewards

240
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:22,480
that kind of emptiness or that desperate seeking to fill that emptiness.

241
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:24,560
Because you know, you get rewarded.

242
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:25,760
You make a lot of money.

243
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:26,960
A lot of people admire you.

244
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,160
You get to feel good about yourself.

245
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:33,600
Mind you, my guess is that good feeling is only temporary.

246
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:37,120
At least if my example is any guided,

247
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,080
feeling good because somebody from the outside values you

248
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:43,680
is only a temporary self for the wound that's inside.

249
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,400
But the world actually rewards it.

250
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,560
You know, so your workaholic doctor, great,

251
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:50,880
you make more money and all these people respect you.

252
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:54,160
Meanwhile, you're hollowing yourself from the inside

